**Why Is Working in a Group Better Than Working Independently?**

Some people might consider that working alone is better since they could have their own plan, and they can do whatever they want instead of being affected by other opinions. However, I believe that working in a group is better because I can learn from others when I listen to their ideas and I can also get some useful information from them. For instance, I took an American literature course last semester, and the instructor asked us to finish a project with other classmates. I spent lots of time on doing the project, and I really enjoyed discussing with others about the topic that we all were interested in even though we spent lots of time on reaching a consensus. However, I learned so much from others, and some of the ideas were really creative and intriguing. To summarize, according to my experiences, I firmly believe that working a group is absolutely better than working individually.



