**Four steps for creating a perfect travel itinerary**

Creating a perfect travel itinerary might seem like a lot of work. There are lots of parts to your trip that need to be organized such as plane tickets, hotel reservations, and restaurant reservations. On top of that, you need to pick out and schedule all of your activities and sightseeing. First, create an inspiration board. You know where you’re travelling to, but the destination is just the beginning of your journey. There’s such a wealth of information online to help guide your planning, so create an inspiration board to keep it organized and in one place. Secondly, organize the essentials. Add your essential travel information to your itinerary, which includes airline tickets, hotel reservations, rental car confirmations and restaurant reservations. Third, add in your activities. You can add some great and interesting activities into your itinerary. Last, leave time for exploration. You have everything scheduled does not mean that you have to follow your itinerary. If you give yourself some room for flexibility, your trip will be much more rewarding.



