**Why is it important to join clubs?***

Some people may consider that joining clubs is waste of time and it would be a great burden when they also need to work or study at the same time. However, I believe that joining clubs can benefit people a lot due to the following reasons. First of all, when people join clubs, they are forced to get along with people, and it would be a good chance for them to improve their communication skills. Secondly, most clubs usually hold a lot of intriguing activities for members to have fun, and when holding activities, people often face problems such as limited budget, inflexible time schedule and different opinions from others. It is also a great opportunity for them to improve the ability to solve problems and negotiating with others. To sum up, joining clubs can benefit people to some degree because they can learn a lot from doing this.



